Colombian Guerrilla Leader Killed, Two Others Captured 
The Colombian military killed one guerrilla leader and captured two
others in major operations on Monday, army sources said today.
Jose Espedito Cruz Cruz, financial chief of the Policarpa Salavarrienta
Front of the Colombian Revolutionary Armed Forces (FARC), was killed in
Cundidnamarca, the sources said.
The two guerrilla leaders, who were taken prisoner in another
operation, were Gilberto Laverde and Augusto Trujillo Sogamoso.
They confessed to having a list of people the guerrillas planned to
kidnap, the sources said.
